The paper discusses local feature-based image retrieval, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions image representation techniques such as bag-of-visual words (BoVW), Fisher vector, and Vector of Locally Aggregated Descriptors (VLAD), which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. Finally, the paper briefly reviews deep learning-based approaches for image retrieval, which is a popular topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
